Some gunmen on Tuesday night reportedly killed several persons during an invasion of the newly constructed Abia cattle market in Omumauzor in the Ukwa West local area of Abia State, The Nation reports.  It was gathered the midnight attack kept the villagers apprehensive.Meanwhile, security operatives have taken over the area to maintain peace.The Abia State Government recently moved traders from Ahia Udele cattle market to Omumauzor following a fatal truck accident in the area.  Source By Emma Ogbuehi The serene atmosphere in Abia State may have been shattered last night going by reports filtering in that gunmen on Tuesday night killed many persons during an invasion of the newly constructed Abia cattle market in Omumauzor in Ukwa West local area of Abia State. TheNiche gathered… In "Top Stories" Lokpanta (Abia)  The Sheriff Cattle Market, Lokpanta, a community of ``settlers’’ in Abia, has called on the state government to grant it political autonomy. Addressing newsmen on Friday in the market located in Umunneochi Local Government Area, the Secretary of the community, Mr Ahmed Baba, said the autonomy would enhance… In "News" Across the world, 100 days is usually marked by public officials.  It is an occasion to showcase achievements during the period and highlight plans for the future. It is only four days to 100 days since the current Service Chiefs took office on January 26, 2021, precisely 96 days. So… In "Top Stories"